[Student "S"]
{NORTH is just shy of a 2\C opening bid, and when SOUTH shows 13-15 points NORTH 
wants to be in a slam.

NORTH cannot use Blackwood because 4NT would be a natural invitation, but with SOUTH's latest bid 
being 2NT he can use Gerber.

Two Major Aces and two Minor Kings fill the holes in NORTH's hand so he bids 7NT.}

